<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Monodromy Labs — Reliable Intelligence in the Wild</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Monodromy Labs is an AI research company building reliable intelligence in the wild. AIR is the first lab-born system: a data-first approach to autonomous issue resolution and software maintenance." />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #fbfcff;
      --bg-soft: #f3f6fc;
      --bg-blue: #eef4ff;
      --panel: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
      --panel-2: rgba(243, 247, 255, 0.95);
      --line: rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.08);
      --line-strong: rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.16);
      --text: #111827;
      --muted: #52607a;
      --muted-2: #6f7c96;
      --accent: #6d63ff;
      --accent-2: #4a84ff;
      --accent-3: #f2c94c;
      --accent-soft: rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.08);
      --accent-soft-2: rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.08);
      --shadow: 0 20px 70px rgba(44, 68, 120, 0.10);
      --shadow-soft: 0 14px 30px rgba(39, 60, 112, 0.08);
      --radius: 28px;
      --radius-sm: 18px;
      --max: 1220px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      color: var(--text);
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 0% 0%, rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.10), transparent 32%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 100% 0%, rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.10), transparent 25%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #f8faff 42%, #f4f7fd 100%);
      min-height: 100vh;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    canvas#stars {
      position: fixed;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
      opacity: 0.85;
    }


    .mesh,
    .noise,
    .grid {
      position: fixed;
      inset: 0;
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 0;
    }

    .mesh::before,
    .mesh::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      border-radius: 50%;
      filter: blur(70px);
      opacity: 0.45;
    }

    .mesh::before {
      width: 30vw;
      height: 30vw;
      top: 4vh;
      left: -8vw;
      background: rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.16);
    }

    .mesh::after {
      width: 28vw;
      height: 28vw;
      top: 8vh;
      right: -8vw;
      background: rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.15);
    }

    .noise {
      opacity: 0.04;
      background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(17,24,39,0.5) 0.5px, transparent 0.5px);
      background-size: 12px 12px;
    }

    .grid {
      background-image:
        linear-gradient(rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.05) 1px, transparent 1px),
        linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.05) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 64px 64px;
      mask-image: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.30), rgba(0,0,0,0));
    }

    a { color: inherit; text-decoration: underline; }
    img { max-width: 100%; display: block; }

    .wrap {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .container {
      width: min(calc(100% - 32px), var(--max));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .topbar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 20;
      background: rgba(251, 252, 255, 0.74);
      backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.05);
    }

    .nav {
      min-height: 78px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 22px;
    }

    .brand {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 14px;
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .brand-mark {
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      overflow: hidden;
      flex: 0 0 auto;
    }

    .brand-mark .logo-img {
      display: none;
      width: 74%;
      height: 74%;
      object-fit: contain;
    }

    .brand-mark.loaded .logo-img {
      display: block;
    }

    .brand-mark .logo-fallback {
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      width: 74%;
      height: 74%;
      border-radius: 12px;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.14), transparent 52%),
        linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.10), rgba(242, 201, 76, 0.12));
    }

    .brand-mark.loaded .logo-fallback {
      display: none;
    }

    .brand-meta {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      min-width: 0;
      line-height: 1.06;
    }

    .brand-meta strong {
      font-size: 1rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .brand-meta small {
      color: var(--muted-2);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      margin-top: 4px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .nav-links,
    .nav-cta {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .nav-links a,
    .btn {
      padding: 12px 16px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      transition: 180ms ease;
      font-size: 0.96rem;
    }

    .nav-links a {
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .nav-links a:hover {
      background: rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.05);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 48px;
      gap: 10px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.10);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.86);
      color: var(--text);
      font-weight: 600;
      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    }

    .btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
      border-color: rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.18);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    }

    .btn.primary {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(74,132,255,0.95), rgba(109,99,255,0.96));
      color: white;
      border-color: transparent;
      box-shadow: 0 16px 34px rgba(93, 96, 255, 0.24);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 72px 0 52px;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.16fr 0.84fr;
      gap: 30px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      min-height: 42px;
      padding: 0 14px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.84);
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.08);
      color: var(--muted);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .eyebrow .dot {
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-2), var(--accent));
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(74,132,255,0.10);
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 7vw, 6.4rem);
      line-height: 0.94;
      letter-spacing: -0.06em;
      max-width: 13ch;
    }

    .hero p.lead {
      max-width: 60ch;
      font-size: clamp(1.08rem, 1.7vw, 1.28rem);
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 24px 0 0;
    }

    .accent-line {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), var(--accent-2));
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      background-clip: text;
      color: transparent;
    }

    .hero-actions,
    .hero-notes {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    .micro-note {
      color: var(--muted-2);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .hero-card,
    .card,
    .quote-box,
    .manifesto,
    .side-panel {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.08);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
    }

    .hero-card {
      padding: 28px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero-card::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 85% 18%, rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.13), transparent 24%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 10% 0%, rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.14), transparent 26%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .label {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 9px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.08);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      border: 1px solid rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.12);
    }

    .hero-card h2,
    .section-head h2,
    .manifesto h2,
    .quote-box h3,
    .side-panel h3 {
      margin: 16px 0 0;
      line-height: 1.02;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }

    .hero-card h2 {
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
      max-width: 12ch;
    }

    .hero-card p,
    .card p,
    .manifesto p,
    .side-panel p,
    .quote-box p,
    li {
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.72;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .stats {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .stat {
      background: rgba(244, 247, 254, 0.92);
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.06);
      border-radius: 20px;
      padding: 16px;
      box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    }

    .stat strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 1.36rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }

    .stat span {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 6px;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--muted-2);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    section {
      padding: 28px 0;
    }

    .section-head {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: end;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
    }

    .section-head .kicker {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      font-size: 0.74rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .section-head h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem);
      max-width: 13ch;
    }

    .section-head p {
      max-width: 58ch;
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
      justify-self: end;
    }

    .manifesto-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.02fr 0.98fr;
      gap: 22px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .manifesto {
      padding: 30px;
    }

    .manifesto h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 3rem);
      max-width: 12ch;
    }

    .manifesto-prose {
      display: grid;
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .manifesto-claims {
      display: grid;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .card h3 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .card .num {
      display: inline-flex;
      width: 36px;
      height: 36px;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.10);
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .grid-3,
    .grid-2,
    .research-grid,
    .air-grid,
    .people-grid,
    .services-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 18px;
    }

    .grid-3,
    .research-grid,
    .services-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .grid-2,
    .air-grid,
    .people-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .quote-box {
      padding: 28px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .quote-box::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      width: 180px;
      height: 180px;
      right: -40px;
      top: -40px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(242, 201, 76, 0.16), transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .quote-box .quote {
      font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--text);
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin: 18px 0 0;
      max-width: 24ch;
    }

    .quote-box .attribution {
      margin-top: 18px;
      color: var(--muted-2);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .pill-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .pill {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 38px;
      padding: 0 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.74);
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.08);
    }

    .feature-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .feature-icon {
      width: 44px;
      height: 44px;
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      border-radius: 16px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(74, 132, 255, 0.10), rgba(109, 99, 255, 0.10));
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.06);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .side-panel {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .side-panel ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 18px 0 0;
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .side-panel li {
      padding: 14px 14px 14px 48px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: rgba(246, 249, 255, 0.85);
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.06);
      position: relative;
    }

    .side-panel li::before {
      content: "→";
      position: absolute;
      left: 16px;
      top: 12px;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .split-band {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 0.95fr 1.05fr;
      gap: 22px;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .footer {
      padding: 36px 0 54px;
    }

    .footer-shell {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 18px;
      padding: 22px 24px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
      border-radius: 22px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(18, 28, 45, 0.08);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .footer p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted-2);
      font-size: 0.94rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .section-anchor {
      position: relative;
      top: -110px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1100px) {
      .hero-grid,
      .manifesto-grid,
      .split-band,
      .section-head,
      .grid-2,
      .air-grid,
      .people-grid,
      .research-grid,
      .grid-3,
      .services-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .section-head p {
        justify-self: start;
      }

      h1 {
        max-width: 11ch;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 840px) {
      .nav {
        padding: 14px 0;
        align-items: flex-start;
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .nav-links,
      .nav-cta {
        width: 100%;
      }

      .hero {
        padding-top: 42px;
      }

      .hero-card,
      .card,
      .manifesto,
      .quote-box,
      .side-panel {
        padding: 22px;
      }

      .stats {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <canvas id="stars" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
  <div class="mesh" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="noise" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="topbar">
      <div class="container nav">
        <a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Monodromy Labs home">
          <span class="brand-mark" id="brandMark">
            <img class="logo-img" src="assets/logo.svg" alt="Monodromy Labs logo" />
            <span class="logo-fallback">M</span>
          </span>
          <span class="brand-meta">
            <strong>Monodromy Labs</strong>
            <small>Monodromy, LTD · AI research</small>
          </span>
        </a>

        <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Primary">
          <a href="#manifesto">Manifesto</a>
          <a href="#research">Research</a>
          <a href="#air">AIR</a>
          <a href="#people">People</a>
          <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
        </nav>

        <div class="nav-cta">
          <a class="btn" href="#research">What we study</a>
          <a class="btn primary" href="#contact">Start a conversation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="container hero-grid">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">
              <span class="dot"></span>
              Research, prototypes, and foundational work toward ASI
            </div>
            <h1>Reliable intelligence <span class="accent-line">in the wild.</span></h1>
            <p class="lead">
              Monodromy Labs is a AI research company with a long-horizon goal: to build systems that reasons,
              plans, and learns continuously while making its decisions auditable, stable, and safe.
              Today we position ourselves like a non-profit-style research company: open, service-oriented, and obsessed with the foundations.
            </p>
            <div class="hero-actions">
              <a class="btn primary" href="#manifesto">Read the manifesto</a>
              <a class="btn" href="#air">See AIR</a>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-notes">
              <span class="micro-note">Deciphering and implementing the stable thinking processes that carried us from monkey → flight → Moon.</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="hero-card">
            <span class="label">Current positioning</span>
            <h2>A research lab first. Products as consequences.</h2>
            <p>
              We start from a hard question:
              what would it take for an AI to think robustly under novelty, pressure, and incomplete information?
              AIR is the first answer that emerged from that inquiry.
            </p>
            <div class="stats">
              <div class="stat">
                <strong>Manifesto-led</strong>
                <span>Monodromy is framed around principles, methods, and long-term reliability — not feature churn.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat">
                <strong>AIR</strong>
                <span>Our first lab-born system explores data-first software reasoning and autonomous maintenance.</span>
              </div>
              <div class="stat">
                <strong>Hybrid by design</strong>
                <span>We study how probabilistic models and deterministic structures can reinforce each other.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <span id="manifesto" class="section-anchor"></span>
      <section>
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-head">
            <div>
              <div class="kicker">Manifesto</div>
              <h2>What Monodromy Labs believes.</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              This is the current draft of our public manifesto: a statement of intent for how we want to study intelligence,
              build systems, and collaborate with the research community.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="manifesto-grid">
            <article class="manifesto">
              <span class="label">Full manifesto</span>
              <h2>Intelligence must become more than prediction.</h2>
              <div class="manifesto-prose">
                <p>
                  We believe the next generation of intelligent systems will not emerge from scale alone. Large models have shown that
                  knowledge can be compressed into astonishingly efficient pattern machinery, but pattern completion is not yet the same as
                  grounded understanding. Useful intelligence must stay coherent when the world changes, when evidence is partial, when tools fail,
                  and when decisions carry consequences.
                </p>
                <p>
                  For that reason, Monodromy Labs is built around one conviction: reliable AI will come from fusing probabilistic and deterministic
                  elements into a single working ecology. The probabilistic side gives us compression, flexibility, intuition, and broad generalization.
                  The deterministic side gives us invariants, verifiability, memory structure, symbolic precision, and the ability to say why a system did what it did.
                  We do not see these as competing philosophies. We see them as complementary parts of a mature intelligence stack.
                </p>
                <p>
                  We are interested in stable thinking processes: procedures that continue to work under distribution shift, that can be inspected after the fact,
                  that can revise themselves without collapsing, and that remain useful when moved from benchmark theater into the wild. In our view,
                  the future of AI is not stronger generation, but the construction of reasoning systems that can plan, learn continuously,
                  integrate memory, and remain safe because their internal commitments are traceable.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Monodromy Labs therefore treats products as crystallized research. A product matters when it reveals a durable mechanism.
                  A prototype matters when it teaches us something about reliability. A paper matters when it sharpens the map. Our lab exists to build those maps,
                  test them in code, and turn the useful parts into research services, systems, and public artifacts that move the field forward.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <div class="manifesto-claims">
              <article class="card">
                <span class="num">01</span>
                <h3>Intelligence needs structure.</h3>
                <p>
                  Foundation models are powerful, but intelligence becomes durable only when it is scaffolded by memory, constraints,
                  tools, and explicit world interaction.
                </p>
              </article>

              <article class="card">
                <span class="num">02</span>
                <h3>Grounding has many valid forms.</h3>
                <p>
                  World models, RL, RAG, symbolic systems, graphs, simulators, and contracts are not hacks around intelligence.
                  They are among its necessary organs.
                </p>
              </article>

              <article class="card">
                <span class="num">03</span>
                <h3>Auditability is not optional.</h3>
                <p>
                  Systems that affect software, science, or operations must be inspectable. We care about traces, causal paths,
                  confidence, and post-hoc explanation rooted in mechanism.
                </p>
              </article>

              <article class="card">
                <span class="num">04</span>
                <h3>Benchmarks are signals, not destinations.</h3>
                <p>
